Android Sdk tools



In your Android device, enable developer options
Then,
USB debugging - enable it
Disable Permission Monitoring --> enable it.

Connect your device .
Open CMD, When you run the adb devices command in the Command Prompt (CMD),
it will list the devices attached to your computer. If you see the output you provided:
       List of devices attached
       2f5f0d02        device

It means that one device is connected to your computer, and its device ID is 2f5f0d02.
The "device" status indicates that the device is connected and available for communication.
The device ID is a unique identifier assigned to each connected device.

2f5f0d02 - This is would be your devices udid number, that you need to add in the desired capabilities.